    <problem>
        <question id="1">
            <text>What are all four integers $x \gt 0$ for which the
                distance from $(x, 12)$ to the origin is an integer?</text>
        </question>

        <solution>
            <text>5, 9, 16, 35.</text>
            <text>
                **Method I:** We are told there are four solutions. The Pythagorean triples (5, 12,
                13), (9, 12, 15), (12, 16, 20), (12, 35, 37) give us the solutions 5, 9, 16, 35.
            </text>
            <text>
                **Method II:** Let $y = \sqrt{12^2 + x^2}$ and use a calculator's table (or other)
                feature to
                find integral $y$ when $x$ is integral.
            </text>
            <text>
                **Method III:** $12^2 + x^2 = c^2$ so $144 = (c + x)(c - x)$. Now, factor 144.
                Finally, set the larger factor equal to $c+x$, the smaller factor equal to $c-x$ and
                solve. (Find $2c$ by adding the equations.)</text>
